main event: Objects were observed traveling at high speed over Arenda, Columbia, South America on 6 July 1956.
interesting points: The sighting involved a total of 9 objects,The observation was categorized as Ground-Visual,The conclusion on the sighting was noted as 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation', No physical description of the objects was provided, Subsequent investigation indicated that the objects may have been related to military practice firing in the area.
witness description: sighting recorded in a Project 10073 Record Card with no confirmed witnesses specified
